content:
I am a second year PhD student in Harmonic analysis at UCLA. I was born in Barcelona (Catalonia), where I lived most of my life. I moved to Los Angeles in 2016 to finish my Bachelor’s, and to Zurich in 2017 to do a Master’s at ETHZ. Now at UCLA I’m trying to learn some restriction and decoupling theory.
I am currently a “La Caixa” post-graduate fellow. Before that I was an ESOP  fellow at ETHZ.
I have started a list of online seminars to keep track of the dozens of seminars going on this spring.
